jobContext:
As per planned styles need to review in advance to find out risk factor to get preparation before starting size set/pilot garments;
Conduct PP meeting internally for upcoming styles and have skill to make and check finished pattern;
Must have idea about Marker, shade groups, Shrinkage and pattern adjustment for denim and non-denim items;
Supervise and manage the quality control team, including scheduling workloads and providing training and guidance to team members;
Develop and implement quality control procedures for all sewing operations, including measuring garments, checking for defects, and conducting visual inspections;
Monitor and report on quality control performance, identifying any areas of concern and implementing corrective action as necessary;
Discharging duties and responsibilities by maintaining safety and compliance procedure;
Ensure that all equipment used in sewing operations is properly maintained and calibrated to deliver consistent quality results;
Participate in regular meetings with finishing/ IE/ Maintenance/ Production departments to discuss quality-related issues and identify opportunities for improvement
Able to make corrective and preventive action plan to develop and protect the products;
Any other task assigned by the Management.
